metadata.name: Nuer
metadata.description: This Nuer man is from the far west of Ethiopia was displaced from South Sudan.  has a characteristic of six forehead line scars of his group and the most beautiful pattern of dots and curved forms . Facial scarring as extensive as this now appears quite rare in Africa The Nuer people are Nilotic group in east africa and they are pastoralists who herd cattle for a living. Their cattle serve as companions and define their lifestyle. The Nuer call themselves "Naath
